  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance for Vulnerable Populations in Bolivar and Amazonas States, Venezuela</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention aims to mitigate the immediate needs of primary health services, non-food items and food security presented by the vulnerable population living in selected communities, predominantly indigenous, in the states of Amazonas and Bol&#xED;var. Medical teams will be deployed every two months to a sector and spend a weekly period there. This will increase impact within the communities and enable capacity building of local resources. IOM will procure, supply, and install two generators to Hospital Dr Jos&#xE9; Gregorio Hern&#xE1;ndez (Puerto Ayacucho), Amazonas state, and Caicara Hospital (Cede&#xF1;o), Bolivar State, both currently affected by lack of energy. The food security component will contribute to decrease the number of households in which some member skips meals due to scarcity of food through the distribution of food kits. Beneficiaries will be selected with the cooperation of indigenous leaders and a needs assessment with community participation conducted by IOM. Family hygiene kits with COVID-19 components will be delivered in all target communities, the provided quantity of items per kit is expected to last for four weeks for a household composed of four members.</narrative>
  </description>
